<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
The examined specimens match the description of Ulmer (i.e., tibial spur formula 1,2,2), unlike specimens examined by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" author="Quinteiro, FB" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 37" refId="B58" refString="Quinteiro, FB, Calor, AR, 2015. A review of the genus Oecetis (Trichoptera: Leptoceridae) in the Northeastern region of Brazil with the description of 5 new species. PLoS ONE 10 (6): 1 - 37, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" title="A review of the genus Oecetis (Trichoptera: Leptoceridae) in the Northeastern region of Brazil with the description of 5 new species." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" volume="10" year="2015">Quinteiro and Calor (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, for states of Bahia, Mato Grosso, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Paraíba">Paraiba</normalizedToken>
, and Rio Grande do Norte, which presented tibial spur formula 0,2,2. This species is widely distributed in Brazil, including several records in the Northeast region (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" author="Quinteiro, FB" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 37" refId="B58" refString="Quinteiro, FB, Calor, AR, 2015. A review of the genus Oecetis (Trichoptera: Leptoceridae) in the Northeastern region of Brazil with the description of 5 new species. PLoS ONE 10 (6): 1 - 37, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" title="A review of the genus Oecetis (Trichoptera: Leptoceridae) in the Northeastern region of Brazil with the description of 5 new species." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0127357" volume="10" year="2015">Quinteiro and Calor 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" author="Desiderio, GR" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="151 - 171" refId="B20" refString="Desiderio, GR, Barcelos-Silva, P, Souza, WD, Pes, AM, Azevedo, CD, 2017. Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records. Zootaxa 422 (2): 151 - 171, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" title="Caddisflies (Insecta: Trichoptera) from Maranhao State, Northeast Region, Brazil: A new species, checklist, and new geographical records." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4221.2.1" volume="422" year="2017">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Desidério">Desiderio</normalizedToken>
et al. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" author="Souza, WRM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="1 - 10" refId="B76" refString="Souza, WRM, Lima, LRC, Pes, AMO, Pinheiro, U, 2013a. Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil. Journal of Natural History 48 (45-46): 1 - 10, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" title="Trichoptera (Insecta) from Pernambuco State, northeastern Brazil." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933.2013.791948" volume="48" year="2013 a">Souza et al. (2013a)</bibRefCitation>
recorded the occurrence of the species in the Caatinga domain, Amaraji municipality, Pernambuco state (altitude 320 m). This study provides the first record of species in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Brejo de Altitude</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
